text.tspan: The main dashboard in the Flood Water Detection system serves as the central information hub, displaying the current
conditions of the water monitoring system. On this dashboard, users can view real-time water level status, the active
system mode, and early warning notifications if a rise in water level is detected that may potentially cause flooding.
This system features three operational modes, each designed with its own specific function and purpose to ensure
optimal performance in different environmental conditions.
